<notes>
<act>
<chapter name="Keyboard Shortcuts" numbered="true">
<scene>
<p>This is a quick guide to keyboard shortcuts. Note that many buttons and menus now display either a tooltip or other information about the available shortcuts. Because of this, you do not need to memorize everything.</p>
<br/>
<p><b>Character styles:</b></p>
<p>Ctrl-B - Bold</p>
<p>Ctrl-I - Italic</p>
<br/>
<p><b>Paragraph styles</b> (markups &amp; shortcut):</p>
<p>Ctrl-Alt-0 | Regular text</p>
<p>=&gt; | Ctrl-Alt-B | Bookmark</p>
<p>// | Ctrl-Alt-C | Comment</p>
<p>!! | Ctrl-Alt-M | Missing text</p>
<p>@@  | Tag element</p>
<br/>
<p><b>Scene styles:</b></p>
<p>## | Ctrl-Alt-3 | Regular scene</p>
<p>&gt;&gt; | Ctrl-Alt-S | Synopsis</p>
<p>%% | Ctrl-Alt-N | Notes</p>
<br/>
<p><b>Chapters and Acts:</b></p>
<p>** | Ctrl-Alt-1 | Act</p>
<p># | Ctrl-Alt-2 | Chapter</p>
<br/>
<p><b>Other shortcuts:</b></p>
<br/>
<p>Folding:</p>
<p>Alt-F - Toggle fold</p>
<p>Alt-A - Fold all</p>
<p>Alt-S - Unfold (show) all</p>
<br/>
<p>Search:</p>
<p>Ctrl-F - Search</p>
<p>Ctrl-G - Find next</p>
<p>Ctrl-Shift-G - Find previous</p>
<br/>
<p>Other:</p>
<p>Ctrl-O - Open file</p>
<p>Ctrl-N - New file</p>
<p>Ctrl-S - Save file</p>
<p>Ctrl-W - Close file</p>
<br/>
</scene>
</chapter>
</act>
</notes>
